[[Category:Jamaican Slangs]]
'''Junjo''' is a Jamaican term for the word Mildew. It is also a slang used to describe something with a bad odor. "You smell like junjo."

== History ==

The origins of this word is unknown.

== Songs ==

The term junjo has been used in reggae/dancehall music. Most recently through a song done by Elephant Man, titled "junjo" on the icebreaker riddim.